{{head|zh|hanzi}}

# to [[cover]]
#* {{zh-x|夫{fú} 天 無 不 覆，地 無 不 載。|There is nothing which Heaven does not '''cover''', and nothing which Earth does not sustain.|ref=Zhuangzi}}
# to [[tip over]]; to [[overturn]]; to [[flip]] over
#: {{zh-x|鼎 覆{phak} 過{kè}來。|The wok flipped over.|MN}}
#* {{zh-x|君 者，舟 也。庶人 者，水 也。水 則 載 舟，水 則 覆 舟。故 君 人 者，欲 安，則 莫 若 平政 愛民 矣。|The ruler is the boat; the common people are the water. The water carries the boat; the water '''overturns''' the boat. Thus, should the ruler wish for stability, there is nothing better than to govern with equity and to care for the people.|ref=Xunzi}}
